def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    levels = [index.levels[index._get_level_number(i)] if isinstance(i, tuple) else index.levels[i] for i in clocs]
    codes = [index.codes[index._get_level_number(i)] if isinstance(i, tuple) else index.codes[i] for i in clocs]
    names = [index.names[index._get_level_number(i)] if isinstance(i, tuple) else index.names[i] for i in clocs]

    shape = [len(x) for x in levels]
    group_index = get_group_index(codes, shape, sort=False, xnull=False)

    comp_ids, obs_ids = compress_group_index(group_index, sort=False)
    recons_codes = decons_obs_group_ids(comp_ids, obs_ids, shape, codes, xnull=False)

    if set(clocs) == set(range(index.nlevels)):  # If all levels are unstacked, create a regular index.
        dummy_index = Index(obs_ids, name="__placeholder__")
    else:
        dummy_index = MultiIndex(
            levels=levels + [obs_ids],
            codes=codes + [comp_ids],
            names=names + ["__placeholder__"],
            verify_integrity=False,
        )

    dummy = data.copy()
    dummy.index = dummy_index

    unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)

    return unstacked
